    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The Gaussian image pyramid kernel is enqueued as an in-place operation using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metalperformanceshaders/mpsunaryimagekernel/1618873-encode",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method. All mip-map levels (after level 1) present in the provided image are filled using the provided filter kernel. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "fallbackCopyAllocator",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter is not used. The Gaussian image pyramid kernel ignores the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metalperformanceshaders/mpsunaryimagekernel/1618859-cliprect",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metalperformanceshaders/mpsunaryimagekernel/1618884-offset",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " properties, and fills the entirety of the mip-map levels. Recall the size of the nth mip-map level as:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "w_n = max(1, floor(w_0 / 2^n))",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "h_n = max(1, floor(h_0 / 2^n))",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Where ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "w_0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "h_0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " are the width and height of the 0th level, respectively (i.e. the image dimensions themselves).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The Gaussian image pyramid is constructed as follows:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "First, the 0th level mip-map of the input image is filtered with the specified convolution kernel. The default convolution filter kernel is ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "k = ww^T",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", where ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "w = [1/16, 1/4, 3/8, 1/4,  1/16 ]^T",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ". You may also modify this kernel with a ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "centerWeight",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " parameter of ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "a",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " resulting in ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "k = ww^T",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", where ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "w = [(1/4 - a/2), 1/4, a, 1/4, (1/4 - a/2) ]^T",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", or you may provide a completely custom kernel.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Afterwards, the image is down-sampled by removing all odd rows and columns, which defines the next level in the Gaussian image pyramid.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "This procedure is continued until every mip-map level present in the image is filled with all the pyramid levels.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Make sure your chosen texture type is compatible with mip-mapping and also supports texture views (i.e. the textureâ€™s usage includes the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLTextureUsage/pixelFormatView",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " option).",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
